parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the headlight ballast can cause the headlights to malfunction or fail, leading to reduced visibility and increased risk of accidents, especially at night.
symptoms: Intermittent or complete failure of the headlights
including high and low beams
and daytime running lights; shattered or broken bulbs; and faulty or malfunctioning headlight assemblies.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The defective design of the headlight housing can cause the bulbs to shatter or fail prematurely, leading to reduced visibility and increased risk of accidents, especially at night.
symptoms: Shattered or broken bulbs
faulty or malfunctioning headlight assemblies
and intermittent or complete failure of the headlights
including high and low beams
and daytime running lights.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the high beam headlights can cause reduced visibility and increased risk of accidents, especially at night, and can also lead to police stops and fines.
symptoms: Failure of the high beam headlights
including shattered or broken bulbs
and faulty or malfunctioning headlight assemblies.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Telescoping Steering Column Adjustment Lever Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the telescoping steering column adjustment lever can cause the steering wheel to collapse or move unexpectedly, making it difficult to control the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The steering wheel telescopes down unexpectedly
the steering wheel collapses
the steering column adjustment lever comes loose
the steering wheel moves unexpectedly
the vehicle is difficult to control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering unit can cause the vehicle to lose power steering, making it difficult to control the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The power steering unit is leaking
the power steering boot is torn
the return hose is faulty.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the horn can cause the vehicle to be unable to alert other drivers or pedestrians, which can lead to accidents or safety issues.
symptoms: The horn works intermittently
the horn does not work at all.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended acceleration can cause loss of vehicle control, accidents, and injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates suddenly and unexpectedly
often without the driver's input
making it difficult to control the vehicle. This can occur when driving at various speeds
including slow speeds
and may be accompanied by a failure of the brakes to respond.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Problems with the accelerator pedal can cause unintended acceleration, hesitation, or difficulty accelerating, leading to accidents or loss of vehicle control.
symptoms: The accelerator pedal may stick
hesitate
or be difficult to press
causing the vehicle to accelerate unexpectedly or fail to accelerate when needed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Malfunctions with the cruise control system can cause unintended acceleration, loss of vehicle control, and accidents.
symptoms: The cruise control system may malfunction
causing the vehicle to accelerate unexpectedly or fail to respond to input.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the brake override system can cause unintended acceleration, loss of vehicle control, and accidents.
symptoms: The brake override system may not function properly
allowing the vehicle to accelerate even when the brakes are applied.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure to properly address recall issues can lead to continued safety risks and a lack of confidence in the vehicle.
symptoms: Toyota's response to recalls
including the sticky accelerator pedal and floor mat entrapment recalls
has been inadequate
leading to frustration and concern among vehicle owners.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the headlight assembly can cause the headlights to suddenly stop working, leading to reduced visibility and increased risk of accidents, especially at night or in low-light conditions.
symptoms: Headlights and/or daytime running lights fail to illuminate
headlights turn off intermittently
high beam bulbs shatter inside the headlamp housing
low beam lights burn out
instrument panel lighting turns off.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Intermittent electrical system failures can cause various safety-critical systems to malfunction, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: VSC and engine check lights illuminate intermittently
electrical system malfunctions
instrument panel lighting turns off.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the high beam function can reduce visibility and increase the risk of accidents, especially in rural areas with no streetlights.
symptoms: High beams do not work
high beam bulbs burn out frequently
high beam function is unreliable.
